Constructor Detail

IndexedSet

public IndexedSet(java.util.Collection<T> universe,
                  boolean compressed)
Create an empty IndexedSet based on a given collection that represents the set of all possible items that can be added to the IndexedSet instance.

VERY IMPORTANT! to correctly work and effectively reduce the memory allocation, new instances of IndexedSet must be created through the clone() or emptySet() methods and not by calling many times this constructor with the same collection for universe!

Parameters:
universe - collection of all possible items. Order will be preserved.
compressed - true if a compressed internal representation should be used

powerSet

public java.util.List<? extends IndexedSet<T>> powerSet()
Computes the power-set of the current set.

It is a particular implementation of the algorithm Apriori. The power-set does not contains the empty set. The list is sorted according to the lexicographical order provided by the sorted set.

Overrides:
powerSet in class ExtendedSet<T>
Returns:
the power-set

powerSet

public java.util.List<? extends IndexedSet<T>> powerSet(int min,
                                                        int max)
Computes a subset of the power-set of the current set, composed by those subsets that have cardinality between min and max.

It is a particular implementation of the algorithm Apriori. The power-set does not contains the empty set. The list is sorted according to the lexicographical order provided by the sorted set.

Overrides:
powerSet in class ExtendedSet<T>
Parameters:
min - minimum subset size (greater than zero)
max - maximum subset size
Returns:
the power-set
